This paper deals with energy harvesting and wireless energy transfer in communication networks, which are topics related to information theory (cs.IT) and networking (cs.NI). The paper also discusses energy management policies and optimization, which are relevant to systems and control (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of algorithms, which could fall under multimedia (cs.MM) or distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
